<dl id="n08178o"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08178o">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08178o"> 178(o)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> try to tell a tale / rivals contradict</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In the system of professional training <font color="green">[of bardic historians]</font>, the school itself was a check on tradition. Each man had to repeat what he had learnt in the presence of rivals who would be eager to detect a departure from what had been taught to themselves. <small> Stephen Gwynn, <a name="SGHI" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SGHI"><cite title="source">The History of Ireland</cite></a> (1923) 11</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c03040f" href="c3all.htm#c03040f">VI.C.03:040(f)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
